<p>Here is a parent class</p>  <pre><code>public class Parent {     public void f() {      } } </code></pre>  <p>Here is a simple interface</p>  <pre><code>public interface If {     public void f(); } </code></pre>  <p>Here is a child class</p>  <pre><code>public class Child extends Parent implements If{} </code></pre>  <p>My question is:  Although it is <code>Child</code> which claims to implement the interface <code>If</code>, the interface method is implemented in <code>Parent</code>. Why is this allowed?</p>